# Downing Jones API

The Downing Jones API allows for data requests on
stock market exchanges, companies, locations, and currencies.

# Downing Jones API Root [/api]
This resource does not have any attributes. Instead it offers the initial API affordances in the form of the links in the JSON body.

It is recommend to follow the “url” link values to retrieve resources.
## Retrieve Entry Points [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "exchange_url": "/exchange",
            "company_url": "/company",
            "location_url": "/location",
            "currency_url": "/currency"
        }


## Group Stock Market Exchanges

Resources related to stock exchanges in the API.

## Exchange [/exchange/{exchange_id}]

A Exchange object has the following attributes:

+ id
+ name
+ exchange_symbol
+ market_cap
+ currency
+ location

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number) - Name of the Exchange in form of a number

### View an Exchange's Details [GET]


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            "exchange": 
            {
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "NYSE",
                    "location": "USA",
                    "currency": "US Dollars",
                    "points": 4862.57,
                    "change": +.041%
                }
            }            
        ]

## Exchanges Collection [/exchange{?page}]

+ Parameters
    + page: 1 (optional, number) - The page of exchanges to return

### List All Exchanges [GET]

